cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a visual-textual co-grounding module to locate instructions from surrounding images. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper introduces a self-monitoring agent with two complementary components to navigate in unknown environments. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper deals with an agent following navigational instructions. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper involves natural language processing to understand and follow instructions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of the agent through a series of ablation studies.
